{
  "stem": "17761.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 83.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I came to Bucharest, at that time, you were not authorized to-- to live in Bucharest without a special authorization, which naturally I didn't have.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I had to sneak in illegally into Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Once you were there, you were there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But you couldn't go in there where Romanian Army around the highways, and they were asking everybody for such a permit.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The youth movement-- the Zionist youth movement at that time was full of initiative and very badly organized.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we were a bunch of youngsters, idealistic people, and we tried to organize in all the places and cities of Romania groups of youths In some places, we organized [NON-ENGLISH], we called them, or preparatory branches.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they-- there, we prepared for agricultural life in Israel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We organized regional meetings.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We organized summer camps.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We didn't organize any winter camps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We didn't have this idea at that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there was such a fraternity, first of all, within the youth movement, and despite competition between the youth movements, because we had all one goal-- somehow to leave this cursed land of Europe and go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Naturally, at that time-- whoever knows history-- the British had the White Book.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And according to the White Book, they didn't authorize people to come to Israel.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So the [INAUDIBLE], the Haganah started to struggle [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] against this White Book and to organize task force of Jews into Palestine.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "By the way, it wasn't only the Haganah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There was also the [NON-ENGLISH], which was the right-wing organization, which had even started earlier to organize such little ship.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But on a big scale, there was mainly the Haganah.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At the beginning, they were sent to a place, Atlit.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had a camp in Israel next to Haifa-- to Atlit.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
